Of course, isothermality is imposed only along a contour.  But since the isothermal relations are analytic in character, they extend from the contour to its interior.  In order that the contour integral for  be useful, we must impose isothermality on the functions appearing in it.  A useful starting point in  is the Enneper-Weierstrass construction, which reduces isothermality to an identity.

