The contour form of the Dirichlet area can be interpreted in terms of Abelian gauge potentials, as we now take up.

Area and Abelian gauge potentials 



In any dimension  the area can be expressed as a sum of  contour integrals over  Abelian gauge potentials, which are derived from the complex coordinates . Moreover, we can implement gauge transformations on these potentials and show, as expected, that they do not affect the area.  

